<br>
Just followed the General around until the mobs spawned, then jumped all over them, mostly one group per mob. Only one death if I recall (to a bunch of adds on a lowish caster) but other than that it was fairly easy. Although the General managed to get the killing blow on a couple of mobs and probably ate a Snowchipper <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
So long as you make sure to get aggro off the General as fast as  possible, it's pretty easy if you have sufficient forces (4 groups is probably overkill). Just bring lots of melees, enough healers to keep em alive, and a good slower. Chanter is optional if you have enough people <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
--<br>
Carlo Curiosus, 61 Sorceror, Morell-Thule<br>
